<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">127. Cooper Union Museum. The Logic and Magic of Color. New York: Cooper Union, 1960. Bibl. B/W illus. 36 pp. </p><p class="annot">This catalog for an exhibition of 300 objects held from April 20 to August 31, 1960 features a 16 page essay by Edward Kallop that sweeps in literary, historical and color science sources. Also of interest is the 125 item unannotated bibliography organized into sections on color and light, nature and color chemistry, visual phenomena, terminology and color measurement, and color and human response. The paper stock and inks used to print the catalog were chosen according to Faber Birren’s research studies to produce 80% contrast for minimum eye fatigue. </p></div>
